{"title_page": "Shinichi Sekizawa", "text_new": "{{more citations needed|date=May 2019}}\n{{nihongo|'''Shinichi Sekizawa'''|\u95a2\u6ca2\u65b0\u4e00|Sekizawa Shin'ichi}} (June 2, 1921 in [[Kyoto, Japan]] &ndash; November 19, 1992) was a [[Japan]]ese [[screenwriter]]. His very first screenplay was for the independently produced film (though distributed by [[Shintoho]] Studios) ''Fearful Attack of the Flying Saucers'', which was also his sole directing credit. \n\nHe went on to script several films by [[Ishir\u014d Honda]], including several classic [[Godzilla]] films. He also contributed material to the original ''[[Ultraman (1966 TV series)|Ultraman]]'' series and several [[Toei Animation|T\u014dei D\u014dga]] films such as ''[[Jack and the Witch]]''.\n\nHis scripts for [[kaiju]] films have been noted for their inventiveness and for having a more lightweight, \"fun\" tone than those written by [[Takeshi Kimura]] (aka Kaoru Mabuchi), another leading writer of kaiju films, whose scripts had a darker, more serious sensibility. <!-- See the commentary track on the Classic Media/Sony DVD of Ghidorah, The Three-Headed Monster -->\n\nBefore embarking on his screenwriting career, he briefly attended an animation school with famed [[manga]] artist and animator [[Osamu Tezuka]].\n\n==Partial filmography==\n:Note: The films listed as N/A are not necessarily chronological.\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\"\n! width=\"15%\" rowspan=\"2\" scope=\"col\" | Title !! width=\"4%\" rowspan=\"2\" scope=\"col\" | Year!! colspan=\"3\" scope=\"col\" | Credited as !! width=\"10%\" rowspan=\"2\" scope=\"col\" class=\"unsortable\"| Notes !! width=\"1%\" rowspan=\"2\" scope=\"col\" class=\"unsortable\" |{{abbr|Ref(s)|Reference(s)}}\n|-\n! width=6% | Screenwriter!! width=6% |Screen story author!! width=6% | Other\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|''[[Varan the Unbelievable]]''\n|1958\n| {{yes}}\n| \n|\n| \n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|{{sfn|Galbraith IV|1996|p=425}}{{sfn|Galbraith IV|1996|p=426}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|''[[Battle in Outer Space]]''\n|1959\n| {{yes}}\n| \n|\n| \n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|{{sfn|Galbraith IV|1996|p=113}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|{{sort|Last Gunfight|''[[The Last Gunfight]]''}}\n|rowspan=\"3\"|1960\n| {{yes}}\n| \n|\n| \n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|{{sfn|Galbraith IV|2008|p=165}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|''[[Take Aim at the Police Van]]''\n| {{yes}}\n| \n|\n| \n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nikkatsu.com/movie/20415.html|publisher=[[Nikkatsu]]|title=\u300c\u5341\u4e09\u53f7\u5f85\u907f\u7dda\u300d\u3088\u308a\u3000\u305d\u306e\u8b77\u9001\u8eca\u3092\u72d9\u3048|accessdate=December 12, 2019|language=Japanese|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170830233824/https://www.nikkatsu.com/movie/20415.html|archivedate=August 30, 2017}}</ref>\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|{{sort|Secret of the Telegian|''[[The Secret of the Telegian]]''}}\n| {{yes}}\n| \n|\n| \n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|{{sfn|Galbraith IV|1996|p=349}}{{sfn|Galbraith IV|1996|p=350}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|''Moriya Hirosho no sandogasa shirizu - Nakito gozansu''\n|rowspan=\"2\"|1961\n| {{yes}}\n| \n|\n| \n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|{{sfn|Galbraith IV|2008|p=183}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|''[[Mothra (film)|Mothra]]''\n| {{yes}}\n| \n|\n| \n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|{{sfn|Galbraith IV|2008|p=183}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|''[[King Kong vs. Godzilla]]''\n|1962\n| {{yes}}\n| \n|\n| \n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|{{sfn|Galbraith IV|2008|p=294}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|''[[Warring Clans]]''\n|rowspan=\"3\"|1963\n| {{yes}}\n| \n|\n| \n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|{{sfn|Galbraith IV|2008|p=200}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|{{sort|Lost World of Sinbad|''[[The Lost World of Sinbad]]''}}\n| {{yes}}\n| \n|\n| \n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|{{sfn|Galbraith IV|2008|p=205}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|''[[Atragon]]''\n| {{yes}}\n| \n|\n| \n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|{{sfn|Galbraith IV|1996|p=105}}{{sfn|Galbraith IV|1996|p=106}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|''[[Mothra vs. Godzilla]]''\n|rowspan=\"4\"|1964\n| {{yes}}\n| \n|\n| \n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|{{sfn|Galbraith IV|2008|p=210}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|''Operation Lion Ant''\n| {{yes}}\n| \n|\n| \n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|{{sfn|Galbraith IV|2008|p=210}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|{{sort|Keg of Powder|''A Keg of Powder''}}\n| {{yes}}\n| \n|\n| \n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|{{sfn|Galbraith IV|2008|p=210}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|''[[Ghidorah, the Three-Headed Monster]]''\n| {{yes}}\n| \n|\n| \n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|{{sfn|Galbraith IV|2008|p=215}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|''[[Invasion of Astro-Monster]]''\n| 1965\n| {{yes}}\n| \n|\n| \n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|{{sfn|Galbraith IV|1996|p=292}}{{sfn|Galbraith IV|1996|p=293}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|''[[Ebirah, Horror of the Deep]]''\n| 1966\n| {{yes}}\n| \n|\n| \n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|{{sfn|Galbraith IV|2008|p=234}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|''[[Son of Godzilla]]''\n| 1967\n| {{yes}}\n| \n|\n| \n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|{{sfn|Galbraith IV|2008|p=244}}{{sfn|Galbraith IV|2008|p=245}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|''[[Latitude Zero (film)|Latitude Zero]]''\n|rowspan=\"2\"|1969\n| {{yes}}\n| \n|{{yes}}\n| Screenwriter in Japanese version. Credited as \"Screenplay advisor\" in American prints.\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|{{sfn|Galbraith IV|1996|p=261}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|''[[All Monsters Attack]]''\n| {{yes}}\n| \n|\n| \n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|{{sfn|Ryfle|1998|p=196}}{{sfn|Galbraith IV|1996|p=197}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|''[[Godzilla vs. Gigan]]''\n| 1972\n| {{yes}}\n| \n|\n| \n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|{{sfn|Ryfle|1998|p=190}}{{sfn|Galbraith IV|1996|p=191}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|''[[Godzilla vs. Megalon]]''\n| 1973\n| \n| {{yes}}\n|\n| \n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|{{sfn|Ryfle|1998|p=360}}{{sfn|Galbraith IV|1996|p=193}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|''[[Godzilla vs. Mechagodzilla]]''\n| 1974\n| \n| {{yes}}\n|\n| \n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|{{sfn|Galbraith IV|1994|p=352}}\n|-\n|}\n\n== References ==\n;Citations\n{{reflist}}\n===Bibliography===\n{{Refbegi