\u014dei D\u014dga]] films such as ''[[Jack and the Witch]]''.\n\nHis scripts for [[kaiju]] films have been noted for their inventiveness and for having a more lightweight, \"fun\" tone than those written by [[Takeshi Kimura]] (aka Kaoru Mabuchi), another leading writer of kaiju films, whose scripts had a darker, more serious sensibility. <!-- See the commentary track on the Classic Media/Sony DVD of Ghidorah, The Three-Headed Monster -->\n\nBefore embarking on his screenwriting career, he briefly attended an animation school with famed [[manga]] artist and animator [[Osamu Tezuka]].\n\n==Partial filmography==\n:Note: The films listed as N/A are not necessarily chronological.\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\"\n! width=\"15%\" rowspan=\"2\" scope=\"col\" | Title !! width=\"4%\" rowspan=\"2\" scope=\"col\" | Year!! colspan=\"3\" scope=\"col\" | Credited as !! width=\"10%\" rowspan=\"2\" scope=\"col\" class=\"unsortable\"| Notes !! width=\"1%\" rowspan=\"2\" scope=\"col\" class=\"unsortable\" |{{abbr|Ref(s)|Reference(s)}}\n|-\n! width=6% | Screenwriter!! width=6% |Screen story author!! width=6% | Other\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|''[[Varan the Unbelievable]]''\n|1958\n| {{yes}}\n| \n|\n| \n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|{{sfn|Galbraith IV|1996|p=425}}{{sfn|Galbraith IV|1996|p=426}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|''[[Battle in Outer Space]]''\n|1959\n| {{yes}}\n| \n|\n| \n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|{{sfn|Galbraith IV|1996|p=113}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|{{sort|Last Gunfight|''[[The Last Gunfight]]''}}\n|rowspan=\"3\"|1960\n| {{yes}}\n| \n|\n| \n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|{{sfn|Galbraith IV|2008|p=165}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|''[[Take Aim at the Police Van]]''\n| {{yes}}\n| \n|\n| \n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nikkatsu.com/movie/20415.html|publisher=[[Nikkatsu]]|title=\u300c\u5341\u4e09\u53f7\u5f85\u907f\u7dda\u300d\u3088\u308a\u3000\u305d\u306e\u8b77\u9001\u8eca\u3092\u72d9\u3048|accessdate=December 12, 2019|language=Japanese|archiveurl=https